// `wasmEmit.vl` — the emitter's LOWERING core: the statement / expression
// lowerers (`emitStmt`/`emitExpr` and the per-node `emit*` families — calls,
// assignment, object/array/map construction, unions, closures, string and list
// ops, coalescing) that turn arena nodes into WasmGC instruction bytes inside a
// function body. One layer of the emitter module stack: `emit_classify.vl`
// answers what type/rep a node lowers as, `emit_collect.vl` pre-fills the
// shared tables, `emit_rewrite.vl`/`emit_mono.vl` mutate the arena first,
// `emit_bytes.vl` owns the byte encodings, `emit_state.vl` the shared globals,
// and `emit_sections.vl` above drives `emitProgram`'s pass table and assembles
// the final module sections around the bodies lowered here.
